  <summary>6/23/1999--Introduced.
Alternative Minimum Tax Reform Act of 1999 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a corporation to use, as specified, long-term unused credits against the minimum tax.Allows a ten-year carryback, for purposes of the alternative tax net operating loss deduction, in the case of a corporation that has a net operating loss for three or more consecutive years.</summary>
